# Frontend Architecture — mandatory structure (UPDATED)

**Deprecated (do not use for new work):** `app/features/`, per-entity service factories under `app/services/[entity]/`, and any feature-folder nesting described in older versions of this rule.

The project MUST follow the map below. Cursor must treat this as non-negotiable unless the user explicitly changes it.

---

## 1. Mandatory folder & file map

```text
└── src
    ├── pages/
    │   ├── ProductList.tsx
    │   └── MovementForm.tsx
    ├── components/
    │   ├── ProductCard.tsx
    │   ├── StockBadge.tsx
    │   └── MovementForm.tsx    # UI component (name collision with page is intentional per map; import with aliases if needed)
    ├── services/
    │   └── api.ts               # Single source: Axios + TanStack Query hooks
    └── e2e/                     # Playwright
        ├── product-list.spec.ts
        └── movement-form.spec.ts
```

- **`src/pages/`**: Only route-level composition and wiring (import UI from `src/components/`, call hooks from `src/services/api.ts`). No nested folders unless the user explicitly asks.
- **`src/components/`**: Presentational/feature UI named above; **no nested folders** unless the user explicitly asks.
- **`src/services/api.ts`**: The **only** module for outbound HTTP: Axios client configuration, endpoints, and **all** `useQuery` / `useMutation` hooks. Pages and components MUST NOT define server-fetch hooks elsewhere.
- **`src/e2e/`**: Playwright specs; **kebab-case** file names (e.g. `product-list.spec.ts`).

**Exception — shadcn primitives:** Installing components via the shadcn CLI may create **`src/components/ui/`** for generated primitives only. Do not add other subfolders under `src/components/` or `src/pages/` without explicit user approval.

---

## 2. Component & logic rules

- **Data fetching**: Import React Query hooks **only** from `src/services/api.ts`. Do **not** use `fetch` or Axios directly inside `src/pages/*.tsx` or `src/components/*.tsx`.
- **Business logic**: Keep pages and components thin. Heavy validation/transform pipelines tied to API contracts belong next to the API layer (inside `api.ts` or, if absolutely necessary, small helpers **imported only by `api.ts`** — still no extra folders under `src/services/` unless the user asks).
- **Forms**: Use TanStack Form combined with Zod for form handling and validation (schemas may live in `api.ts` or be imported into `api.ts` from a single adjacent file **only if** the user approves splitting an oversized `api.ts`).
- **10-line rule**: If non-trivial UI logic (handlers, effects, local state orchestration) in a component exceeds ~10 lines, extract a hook **in the same directory** as that component (flat `src/components/` file sibling), unless the logic is purely server-state (then it stays in `api.ts`).

---

## 3. Type system & naming

- **Use `type`, never `interface`** for data shapes and props.
- **Do not use TypeScript `enum`**: use literal unions or `as const` objects.
- **Zod** is the single source of truth for validated API/form shapes; infer TS types with `z.infer<typeof schema>`.
- **Naming**: PascalCase for `src/pages/` and `src/components/` React files; camelCase for variables/functions; **kebab-case** for `src/e2e/*.spec.ts`.

---

## 4. Styling & UI (shadcn/ui & Tailwind)

- Style with **Tailwind CSS**.
- Add UI via **shadcn/ui** using the project’s package runner, e.g. `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <component>` (or `npx` / `bunx` per repo).
- Prefer theme tokens and shared CSS variables over one-off raw colors.

---

## 5. Implementation policy (tickets)

- When a ticket asks to **create a component**, place it under **`src/components/`** using the names from the map when applicable (`ProductCard`, `StockBadge`, movement UI as `MovementForm.tsx`).
- When a ticket asks for a **page**, place it under **`src/pages/`** (`ProductList.tsx`, `MovementForm.tsx`).
- **Do not** introduce `app/features/`, nested feature trees, or per-entity `services/` folders for new work.

---

## 6. Prohibitions

- **NO barrel files**: no `index.ts` / `index.tsx` re-export aggregators.
- **NO manual `interface`** for API/domain shapes (use Zod + `type`).
- **NO server hooks outside `src/services/api.ts`** (no `useQuery` / `useMutation` in pages/components).
